  "gloss": "For heterogeneous target families and probabilistic (PMF) dynamics, the bisimilarity relation is the greatest equivalence that conforms to the targets and the dynamics.\n\n**Cites** `TLT.NonIdentifiability.isGreatest_bisimilarity` — the corpus theorem this result restates and discharges.\n\n**Original contribution.** The corpus lemma gives the greatest conforming equivalence in the probabilistic-kernel setting; the thesis presents it as the concrete kernel-level form of the forcing principle, the version most of the experiment legs below build on.\n",
